What the module does (per docs)

  • Splits traffic for selected User ID submodules according to percentage, then disables the non-selected side using activity controls. The A/B config is optionally stored (or recalculated each load in memory mode) and is attached to analytics labels for reporting. docs.prebid.org

  • Key params:

    • modules[]: { name, percentage }

    • storeSplits: memory | sessionStorage | localStorage

    • suppression: submodules | eids (default eids)

    • testRun: free-text label for your experiment name (e.g., "SharedID Test"). docs.prebid.org

What your page is doing

  • Configures SharedID with Enrichment Lift at 50/50, suppression: 'eids', and storeSplits: 'memory'—so the cohort re-rolls on each load (by design in memory mode). index

  • Wires up Generic Analytics to collectUrl with custom formatter functions and also uses a lightweight “labels tap” to surface the enrichment labels. index

  • Builds a synthetic-vs-Prebid winner path: you bias winners via synthWinRate and add lift to the test cohort via synthLift, then post a compact lift_auction summary (baseline/treatment/incremental + labels) to the collector. index

  • UI: a 300×250 slot, a rerun button that enforces demo params, and a tiny canvas chart that plots treatment CPM points by cohort with trend lines. index

Quick nits / alignment notes

The Enrichment Lift module adds an object to args.labels on every analytics event. // --- PATCH: rely on enrichmentLiftMeasurement labels only ---
function cohortFromELMLabels(ev, { testRun = 'SharedId teset', submodule = 'sharedId' } = {}) {
  const labels = ev && ev.labels;
  const run = labels && labels[testRun];
  if (!Array.isArray(run)) return 'unknown';
  const rec = run.find(o => o && (o.name === submodule || o.name === submodule + 'System'));
  if (!rec || typeof rec.enabled !== 'boolean') return 'unknown';
  return rec.enabled ? 'test' : 'control';
}

Short answer: this is expected. With your current setup the Enrichment Lift “coin toss” happens once per storage scope (page load / session / browser), not per auction—so you’ll keep seeing the same result (e.g., test) for every auction in that session.

Here’s how to verify and how to flip it on demand:

Why you always see test

  • If storeSplits: 'sessionStorage' or 'localStorage', the first toss is persisted. Every subsequent auction in that session/browser will use the same decision.

  • Even with storeSplits: 'memory', the toss happens once per page load. Clicking “Re-run Auction” won’t re-toss; you’d need a reload.

See what’s configured

Option B — Clear the saved split and reload

js
(function(){

You got it — we’ll make the module “re-flip the coin” on every button click by resetting its config right before each auction.

Below is a copy-paste drop-in. It (1) forces a fresh decision each run, (2) gives you a unique testRun per auction so labels don’t collide, and (3) logs the result.

1) Add this block after pbjs.enableAnalytics(...) and before runAuction() is called

html
<script>
// ---- Per-auction coin toss for Enrichment Lift ----
window.__elmRunSeq = 0;
window.__currentRunKey = 'SharedId test'; // last run key
window.__lastAuctionCohort = 'unknown';

/**
 * Call this at the START of every run to force a fresh ELM decision.
 * It flips a coin and sets percentage to 1 (all test) or 0 (all control),
 * uses storeSplits: 'memory', and creates a unique testRun key per auction.
 */
function __setupELMForNextAuction() {
  const forcedPct = Math.random() < 0.5 ? 1 : 0;     // our coin toss
  const runKey = `SharedId test #${++window.__elmRunSeq}`;

  pbjs.setConfig({
    enrichmentLiftMeasurement: {
      testRun: runKey,
      modules: [{ name: 'sharedId', percentage: forcedPct }],
      storeSplits: 'memory',   // re-evaluated each run
      suppression: 'eids'
    }
  });

  window.__currentRunKey = runKey;
  console.log('[ELM next auction]', { runKey, forcedPct });
  return runKey;
}

// Log the coin toss using the labels bundle for the CURRENT run
pbjs.onEvent('auctionEnd', function () {
  const labels = (typeof __computeEnrichmentLabels === 'function') ? __computeEnrichmentLabels() : {};
  const run = Array.isArray(labels[window.__currentRunKey]) ? labels[window.__currentRunKey] : [];
  const rec = run.find(o => o && (o.name === 'sharedId' || o.name === 'sharedIdSystem'));
  const cohort = rec && typeof rec.enabled === 'boolean' ? (rec.enabled ? 'test' : 'control') : 'unknown';
  window.__lastAuctionCohort = cohort;
  console.log('[ELM coin toss]', cohort, run);
});
</script>

  • log [ELM coin toss] test|control [...] after the auction ends

    // look only at THIS page-load's run key
    const run = labels && labels[freshRun];
